<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 2000, 4000 &#38; 8000 MODELS - TROUBLESHOOTING
        - TESTING TRACTION CONTROL SOLENOID ATR-1/ATR-2, PART B
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING TRACTION CONTROL SOLENOID ATR-1/ATR-2, PART B</title>
        <table id="t0403322" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Traction Control Solenoid ATR-1/ATR-2, Part B</title>
            <tgroup cols="6" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.77in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.65in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.65in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (287), measure resistance between terminals D2 and D3 and ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to Step 3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect the traction control solenoid. At controller side of connector measure
                                resistance to ground at both terminals.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Replace the traction control solenoid/pigtail assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate short to ground in chassis harness circuits 94BB and 94BA, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (287), measure resistance between circuits 94BB and 94BA and all other
                                circuits in connector (287).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate short between any circuits where resistance between terminals is less than 100K
                                ohms, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Make sure connectors (287) and at the traction control solenoid are clean, free of
                                damage, and reconnect. Turn key ON and use magnet to reset LEDs. Repeat
                                <hotlnk document="s04033_7.xml" xrefid="t0403301">INITIAL START-UP TEST
                                    PROCEDURE</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
